main event: A civilian observed a UFO in Blytheville, Arkansas on October 24, 1966, which was concluded to be a satellite (Echo II).
interesting points: The object was estimated to be traveling at speeds greater than 1,000 M/H while descending at a very high altitude., The sighting lasted for roughly 1 minute., The object appeared to be traveling northward, moving over the observer's position., The observer, a housewife, expressed confidence that the object sighted was not an aircraft., Two B-52 aircraft were airborne in the area at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object thought to be a satellite
witness description: a civilian housewife in Blytheville, Arkansas
